      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEATSEEKER (5) has been excellent of late. Led to cruise home at Charlton then made it two in a row when successful at his latest appearance at Ballarat, getting home by 7.6 metres. Has placed in both attempts at this circuit and distance. Can land the hat trick. HES NO ROMEO NZ (8) is racing well having recorded back-to-back placings at Melton. Backs up after finishing 4.2 metres from the winner in a higher-graded race on Saturday. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and drops to a distance where he is proven. SERGEANT LOU (7) draws wide but will be fitter for his first-up seventh at Melton and races well at this shorter distance with two wins and a placing from four attempts so can improve. DRESSED IN GOLD NZ (6) placed here last time and is another with a good record at this distance.",
